 more important among women than men, and in Champassack than in Luang Prabang, whereas the time factor was a bigger concern in Luang Prabang than in Champassack. 26 Further, it is worth noting that there was only one non-Lao native speaker among those reporting that the contract was not available in a language they could read. Illiteracy may have been a factor in this regard. Figure\ufffd23:\ufffdReasons\ufffdwhy\ufffdrespondents\ufffddid\ufffdnot\ufffdfully\ufffdor\ufffdat\ufffdall\ufffdunderstand\ufffdtheir\ufffdcontract,\ufffd\ufffd in\ufffdtotal,\ufffdby\ufffdgender\ufffdand\ufffdprovince\ufffdin\ufffdLao\ufffdPDR\ufffd(%) 50 40 30 20 10 0 Total (N=72) Men (N=41) Women (N=31) Luang Prabang (N=23) Champassack (N=49) Contract not in a right language 20.4 4.3 25.8 7.3 15.3 Insufficient time to study contract 6.1 21.7 12.2 9.7 11.1 Terminology too complicated 43.5 42.9 45.2 41.5 43.1 Didn\u2019t read contract 37.5 33.3 33.3 38.6 36.3 Only 40 per cent of the 117 regular migrant workers who signed contracts with their recruitment agency received a copy of their agreement.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "cb81032e-0700-4110-8279-a56226d2fde1": {"__data__": {"id_": "cb81032e-0700-4110-8279-a56226d2fde1", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/whats-incentive", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "What's the Incentive?", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/whats-incentive", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "f0ea675ce7df22066a19fd3b