e workers to higher- skilled jobs rather than pursue layoffs.38 Large brands such as these are sensitive to public opinion and government perception and, as such, layoffs are less likely from national brands than foreign investors (see the section below on mitigating factors). AI could substantially diminish the competitive advantage of English language-speaking in the services sector, hitherto enjoyed by India and the Philippines, although this could also allow economies with other strengths, but lacking a widely spoken global language, to enter the sector. TWO ASIAN ECONOMIES ARE HIGHLY EXPOSED - INDIA AND THE PHILIPPINES. THEIR COMPARATIVE ADVANTAGES, LIKE WIDESPREAD ENGLISH LANGUAGE SKILLS AND LOWER LABOUR COSTS, COULD BOTH PROVE IRRELEVANT 27 A second services sub-sector where employment could be negatively impacted by automation and AI is logistics and fulfilment. Commentators have described e-commerce as helping to offset job losses in manufacturing", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "70872a76-b732-4c55-b81d-f36a3e26b4cd": {"__data__": {"id_": "70872a76-b732-4c55-b81d-f36a3e26b4cd", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/development-40-opportunities-and-challenges-accelerating-progress-towards-sustainable-development-goals-asia-and-pacific", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Development 4.0: Opportunities and Challenges for Accelerating Progress towards the Sustainable Development Goals in Asia and the Pacific", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/development-40-opportunities-and-challenges-accelerating-progress-tow